Depression, it isn’t a war you win. 
It’s a battle you fight every day. 
That feeling of helplessness, hopelessness. 
But you need to realize that your purpose is actually hidden in your pain
and you’re not alone.

Verse 1

Have you ever felt like your drownin’ 
submerged in an ocean of pain 
created by all of the tears from emotion contained 
that you just let out it’s almost like you’ve broken the chain 
finally get out but only to be soaked in the rain
and your depression is a secret that you keep to yourself 
no one to talk to so you’re forced to speak to yourself 
some day it’ll get better is what you repeat to yourself 
seems like that day just never comes so you dig deep in yourself 
just to handle everyday tasks gets worse as everyday passes 
feeling outta place while everybody else in they bag 
they smiling and they happy while you’re downin’ out and stay sad 
want you to know that I know what it’s like and I relate bad 
because I feel the same as you PTSD and OCD that’s just to name a few 
deal with anxiety and stress and gotta tame ‘em too 
like me you should use the pain to ignite the flame in you seems crazy but

"When a group of tourists visited a crocodile farm, the owner of the place launched a bold proposal, "Whoever dares to jump, swim to the shore, and survive, I'll give you $1,000,000.
No one dared to move. Suddenly, a man jumped into the water, and desperately swam, and made it to the shore, while being chased by all the crocodiles.
The owner announced, "We have a brave winner!!"
After the man collected his reward, he and his wife returned to the hotel.
Upon arrival, the manager told him that he had been very brave to jump. To which the man replied, "I didn't jump, someone pushed me!" His wife smiled.....
Moral - Behind every successful man, there's a woman who pushes him! 🤣😂🤣"
